Confirm Magic SysRq is enabled.
Run this once (while you can see the screen):

cat /proc/sys/kernel/sysrq

If the output is 1, it is enabled.

If not, enable it permanently:

echo "kernel.sysrq = 1" | sudo tee /etc/sysctl.d/99-sysrq.conf
sudo sysctl -p /etc/sysctl.d/99-sysrq.conf

Hold Alt + SysRq, then press R E I S U O


R – return control to keyboard
E – end processes
I – kill remaining processes
S – sync disks
U – remount disks read-only
O – power off
